    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Edward Argar was appointed as Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Ministry of Justice on 14 June 2018.</p>

<p>He was elected as Conservative MP for Charnwood in 2015.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4847">
            <h1 id="parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state">Parliamentary Under Secretary of State</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Parliamentary Under Secretary of Stateâ€™s responsibilities are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Victims (including domestic abuse and domestic violence)</li>
  <li>Female offenders</li>
  <li>Youth justice</li>
  <li>Offender health</li>
  <li>Coroners, burials, inquests and inquiries</li>
  <li>Lammy Review</li>
  <li>Race Disparity Audit (in relation to Ministry of Justice policy areas)</li>
  <li>Devolved Administrations (in relation to Ministry of Justice policy areas)</li>
  <li>Justice devolution</li>
  <li>Human rights</li>
  <li>Lawfare</li>
  <li>Transgender offenders</li>
  <li>Veterans (in relation to Ministry of Justice policy areas)</li>
  <li>Mental capacity and Office of the Public Guardian</li>
  <li>Criminal Cases Review Commission</li>
  <li>Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme</li>
</ul>

</div>
